# CI/CD

## Workflows

| Workflow | When | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| [`.github/workflows/kmp-ci.yml`](.github/workflows/kmp-ci.yml) | Push, PR, manual | Android unit+APK, merge-gate instrumented, Supabase migration validation |
| [`.github/workflows/supabase-deploy.yml`](.github/workflows/supabase-deploy.yml) | `main` supabase push, manual | `db push` + deploy `notify-household-invite` / `delete-account` + smoke probe |

### KMP CI jobs (tiered)

- **Feature branch:** open a PR to `main` — one workflow run per push (`pull_request` synchronize only; no duplicate `push` trigger).
- **PR:** `Android CI`, `Supabase Migrations`, and `Android Instrumented UI Tests` in parallel; **no Firebase Release** (merge gate only).
- **Push `main`/`master`:** same jobs as PR, then **Release** (Firebase + version bump). Version bump commits use `[skip ci]` and the **CI gate** skips heavy jobs.
- **Manual dispatch:** `all`, `android-ci`, `android-instrumented-tests`, `supabase-migrations`, `release`. **iOS compile is disabled** (`ios-compatibility` job `if: false`; verify locally with `./gradlew :composeApp:compileKotlinIosSimulatorArm64`).

### Supabase

- **CI validation (no remote writes):** `supabase start` applies migrations and exposes REST for invite preview RPC smoke tests; remote smoke via `scripts/verify-supabase-household.sh` on PR/`main` only. Set `SUPABASE_TEST_EMAIL` + `SUPABASE_TEST_PASSWORD` for authenticated round-trip (export RPC, device token, nutrition persistence).
- **Deploy:** `supabase-deploy.yml` runs `db push`, configures outbox `pg_net` delivery, and edge function deploy on `main` when `supabase/migrations/**`, `supabase/config.toml`, or `supabase/functions/**` change. Migrations: `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD`, `SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF`; optional `SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` for outbox auto-dispatch config. Functions: also `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`; optional `RESEND_API_KEY`, `INVITE_FROM_EMAIL`. Smoke: `scripts/verify-supabase-edge-functions.sh`, `scripts/verify-household-notification-delivery.sh`.
- **Android builds:** `SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` → `local.properties` via composite setup action.
- **`GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON`:** enables Crashlytics in CI debug APKs.

### Release job

- Runs on **`main`/`master` push** and manual `release`/`all` dispatch only — not on PRs.
- Downloads `composeApp-debug-apk`, distributes to Firebase App Distribution, bumps version on **main push** (`chore(version): … [skip ci]`).
- **`release` only dispatch:** reuses APK from latest successful `Android CI` on the branch (or `source_run_id`).

## Change guidelines

- Keep the tiered model: manual/feature work via **workflow_dispatch**; merge gate on PR/`main`.
- Do not run `db push` inside KMP CI — deploy workflow only.
- Never commit secrets; use GitHub Secrets.
- **CI speed:** merged unit+APK; parallel merge-gate jobs; AVD snapshot cache; shallow checkout; Gradle `setup-gradle` cache; pinned `firebase-tools` with npm cache; Supabase validation parallel on PR/`main` only.

## Firebase App Distribution

- Release notes: branch/SHA + QA checklist excerpt from `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml`.
- Update YAML when shipping UX changes.

## Commits & PRs

- Commit only when user asks; match repo commit message style.
- PRs: behavior change, test plan (unit + instrumented + manual), UI screenshots when relevant.

## Artifacts

- Debug APK: `composeApp-debug-apk` (consumed by `Release` job).
